(15, 1, '2012-07-28 01:00:11', '2012-07-28 01:00:11', '<div class="roastParagraphBox">\r\n<p class="paragraph">Brooklyn isn’t known for being mild but we’ve toned it down a little for our BBR Light roast to produce an impeccably balanced coffee with a light, crisp taste. It has a full body and character with a hint of robust nutty overtones but it is light-bodied flavor with a mild finish and aroma.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Enjoy this mellow blend and take in the lighter side of Brooklyn.</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="roastTypeImageBox">\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_76" align="alignleft" width="89"]<a class="fancyBox" href="#breakfast-blend"><img class="size-full wp-image-76  " title="Caps_LightRoasts_Regular" src="http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//////wp-content/uploads/2012/07/Caps_LightRoasts_Regular.png" alt="" width="89" height="87" /></a> Breakfast Blend[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_77" align="alignleft" width="89"]<a class="fancyBox" href="#breakfast-blend-decaf"><img class="size-full wp-image-77  " title="Caps_LightRoasts_Decaf" src="http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//////wp-content/uploads/2012/07/Caps_LightRoasts_Decaf.png" alt="" width="89" height="87" /></a> Breakfast Blend Decaf[/caption]\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Light Roasts', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'light-roasts', '', '', '2012-08-17 02:08:27', '2012-08-17 02:08:27', '', 0, 'http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//////?post_type=bbr_roasts&#038;p=15', 0, 'bbr_roasts', '', 0),
(16, 1, '2012-07-27 16:08:31', '2012-07-27 16:08:31', '<div class="roastParagraphBox">\r\n<p class="paragraph">Like standing in a subway car and holding on to the above-the-head grab bar, making a great medium roast requires a bit of a balancing act. You want to get a strong, rich flavor that stays smooth and has a very even texture all at the same time. Each of the Brooklyn Bean mediums are specially crafted to bring out perfect balance of crisp nuttiness and full bodied smoky flavor for the most extraordinary tasting stuff in a cup.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>There are very few things that Brooklyn does halfway. Lucky for you, a good medium roast coffee is one of them. Enjoy!</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="roastTypeImageBox">\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_271" align="alignleft" width="89"]<a class="fancyBox" href="#brooklyn-bridge-blend"><img class="size-full wp-image-271   " title="brooklynBridge" src="http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta///wp-content/uploads/2012/07/brooklynBridge.png" alt="" width="89" height="87" /></a> Brooklyn Bridge Blend[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_272" align="alignleft" width="89"]<a class="fancyBox" href="#columbian"><img class="size-full wp-image-272  " title="columbian" src="http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta///wp-content/uploads/2012/07/columbian.png" alt="" width="89" height="87" /></a> Columbian[/caption]\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Medium Roasts', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'medium-roasts', '', '', '2012-08-17 02:42:15', '2012-08-17 02:42:15', '', 0, 'http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//////?post_type=bbr_roasts&#038;p=16', 0, 'bbr_roasts', '', 0),
(17, 1, '2012-07-23 16:09:24', '2012-07-23 16:09:24', '<div class="roastParagraphBox">\r\n<p class="paragraph">In Brooklyn,  we know a thing or two about being bold and when we say this coffee is bold you betta believe it’s bold. To get a perfect dark roast, the beans are removed from the roasters right before they become “espresso roasts” so they retain sharp floral notes and all the smoky goodness without any of the burnt aftertaste. When these beans with big-time flavor are brewed through our patented tension based filters they create a cup of Joe that will delight lovers of good strong coffee. The Brooklyn Bean rich &amp; robust dark roasts are as strong and intense as the borough they come from.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>So go ahead, its Brooklyn… Be bold!</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="roastTypeImageBox">\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_274" align="alignleft" width="89"]<a class="fancyBox" href="#cyclone"><img class="size-full wp-image-274 " title="cyclone" src="http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta///wp-content/uploads/2012/07/cyclone.png" alt="" width="89" height="87" /></a> Cyclone[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_275" align="alignleft" width="89"]<a class="fancyBox" href="#fuhgeddaboutit "><img class="size-full wp-image-275   " title="fughet" src="http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta///wp-content/uploads/2012/07/fughet.png" alt="" width="89" height="87" /></a> Fuhgeddaboutit[/caption]\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Dark Roasts', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dark-roasts', '', '', '2012-09-06 11:10:17', '2012-09-06 11:10:17', '', 0, 'http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//////?post_type=bbr_roasts&#038;p=17', 0, 'bbr_roasts', '', 0),
(19, 1, '2012-09-05 14:54:29', '2012-09-05 14:54:29', '<img src="http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//wp-content/uploads/2011/07/coffee-tower-300x200.jpg" alt="" title="coffee tower" width="300" height="200" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-482" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:410;" />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<p class="paragraph"><strong>Marcy Cantone-from Bayside wrote:</strong><br />\nThere is nothing like the excitement of the holidays! I would love to have a few holiday flavors to look forward to. If you made an assorted box just for the holidays you could get them all in!</p>\n\n<p class="paragraph">Candy Cane Coffee: fruity mint</p>\n\n<p class="paragraph">Roasted chestnut flavored Coffee</p>\n\n<p class="paragraph">White Christmas: hot chocolate n’ marshmallows</p>\n\n<div class="divider"></div>\n\n<p class="paragraph"><strong>Kevin from Jacksonville wrote:</strong><br />\nA line of desert coffees would be nice and would go along with Brooklyn Bean being different from the big name coffee companies. It would be more like a line of indie beers. Some of the flavors that I personally would like to see are: Dutch chocolate cake, Apple Pie, Carmel Cream, Girl Scout mints, and Cheese cake.</p>\n\n<div class="divider"></div>\n\n<p class="paragraph"><strong>Mellissa Horne from Carroll Gardens wrote:</strong><br />\nI found that not using tap water and brewing with spring water has a big effect on the taste of the coffee. Im sure that there are even better options for brewing than just regular bottled water- You should come out with Brooklyn Been Coffee water. Water made to brew with. What if you flavored it?! Vanilla bean brewing water! The possibilities are endless! Sign me up!</p>', 'Suggestions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-autosave', '', '', '2012-09-05 14:54:29', '2012-09-05 14:54:29', '', 11, 'http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//////?p=19', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(20, 1, '2012-07-24 14:36:27', '2012-07-24 14:36:27', 'This is an example page. It''s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I''m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin'' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickies to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//////wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!', 'Sample Page', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision', '', '', '2012-07-24 14:36:27', '2012-07-24 14:36:27', '', 2, 'http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//////?p=20', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
