(453, 1, '2012-08-18 03:41:48', '2012-08-18 03:41:48', '<h6><a href="http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Bridge2.png"><img class=" wp-image-402 alignleft" title="Bridge2" src="http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Bridge2.png" alt="" width="600" height="449" /></a></h6>\r\n<h2>We’re three guys from Brooklyn who love coffee--it’s as simple as that.</h2>\r\n<p class="paragraph">We know where to find the best slice, the best donut shop, the perfect apartment on the best block in the right neighborhood. We grew up with an appreciation for quality, originality, and local pride, and we’ve based our company on those values.</p>\r\n<p class="paragraph">We use the highest quality arabica beans for each of our blends and roast them right here in New York. Brooklyn itself is always diverse and never boring, so we offer a variety of flavors to suit every palette.</p>\r\n<p class="paragraph">Our goal is to provide a great cup of coffee that reminds you of the sights and sounds of Brooklyn. Whether you prefer a smooth, mild blend that makes you feel at home, or a rich, dark roast that takes you back to a wild night you spent in the city, Brooklyn Bean Roastery has the perfect blend for you.</p>', 'Our Story', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '117-revision-9', '', '', '2012-08-18 03:41:48', '2012-08-18 03:41:48', '', 117, 'http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//?p=453', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(454, 1, '2012-08-22 13:58:52', '2012-08-22 13:58:52', '<p class="paragraph"><strong>Marcy Cantone-from Bayside wrote:</strong>\r\nThere is nothing like the excitement of the holidays! I would love to have a few holiday flavors to look forward to. If you made an assorted box just for the holidays you could get them all in!</p>\r\nCandy Cane Coffee: fruity mint\r\n\r\nRoasted chestnut flavored Coffee\r\n\r\nWhite Christmas: hot chocolate n’ marshmallows\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class="paragraph"><strong>Kevin from Jacksonville wrote:</strong>\r\nA line of desert coffees would be nice and would go along with Brooklyn Bean being different from the big name coffee companies. It would be more like a line of indie beers. Some of the flavors that I personally would like to see are: Dutch chocolate cake, Apple Pie, Carmel Cream, Girl Scout mints, and Cheese cake.</p>\r\n<p class="paragraph"><strong>Mellissa Horne from Carroll Gardens wrote:</strong>\r\nI found that not using tap water and brewing with spring water has a big effect on the taste of the coffee. Im sure that there are even better options for brewing than just regular bottled water- You should come out with Brooklyn Been Coffee water. Water made to brew with. What if you flavored it?! Vanilla bean brewing water! The possibilities are endless! Sign me up!</p>', 'Suggestions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-10', '', '', '2012-08-22 13:58:52', '2012-08-22 13:58:52', '', 11, 'http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//?p=454', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
