(483, 1, '2012-08-29 23:32:40', '2012-08-29 23:32:40', '<p class="paragraph"><strong>Marcy Cantone-from Bayside wrote:</strong><br />\r\nThere is nothing like the excitement of the holidays! I would love to have a few holiday flavors to look forward to. If you made an assorted box just for the holidays you could get them all in!</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="paragraph">Candy Cane Coffee: fruity mint</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="paragraph">Roasted chestnut flavored Coffee</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="paragraph">White Christmas: hot chocolate n’ marshmallows</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="divider"></div>\r\n\r\n<p class="paragraph"><strong>Kevin from Jacksonville wrote:</strong><br />\r\nA line of desert coffees would be nice and would go along with Brooklyn Bean being different from the big name coffee companies. It would be more like a line of indie beers. Some of the flavors that I personally would like to see are: Dutch chocolate cake, Apple Pie, Carmel Cream, Girl Scout mints, and Cheese cake.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="divider"></div>\r\n\r\n<p class="paragraph"><strong>Mellissa Horne from Carroll Gardens wrote:</strong><br />\r\nI found that not using tap water and brewing with spring water has a big effect on the taste of the coffee. Im sure that there are even better options for brewing than just regular bottled water- You should come out with Brooklyn Been Coffee water. Water made to brew with. What if you flavored it?! Vanilla bean brewing water! The possibilities are endless! Sign me up!</p>', 'Suggestions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-13', '', '', '2012-08-29 23:32:40', '2012-08-29 23:32:40', '', 11, 'http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//?p=483', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(484, 1, '2012-09-05 03:16:35', '2012-09-05 03:16:35', '<img src="http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//wp-content/uploads/2011/07/coffee-tower-300x200.jpg" alt="" title="coffee tower" width="300" height="200" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-482" />\r\n<p class="paragraph"><strong>Marcy Cantone-from Bayside wrote:</strong><br />\r\nThere is nothing like the excitement of the holidays! I would love to have a few holiday flavors to look forward to. If you made an assorted box just for the holidays you could get them all in!</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="paragraph">Candy Cane Coffee: fruity mint</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="paragraph">Roasted chestnut flavored Coffee</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="paragraph">White Christmas: hot chocolate n’ marshmallows</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="divider"></div>\r\n\r\n<p class="paragraph"><strong>Kevin from Jacksonville wrote:</strong><br />\r\nA line of desert coffees would be nice and would go along with Brooklyn Bean being different from the big name coffee companies. It would be more like a line of indie beers. Some of the flavors that I personally would like to see are: Dutch chocolate cake, Apple Pie, Carmel Cream, Girl Scout mints, and Cheese cake.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="divider"></div>\r\n\r\n<p class="paragraph"><strong>Mellissa Horne from Carroll Gardens wrote:</strong><br />\r\nI found that not using tap water and brewing with spring water has a big effect on the taste of the coffee. Im sure that there are even better options for brewing than just regular bottled water- You should come out with Brooklyn Been Coffee water. Water made to brew with. What if you flavored it?! Vanilla bean brewing water! The possibilities are endless! Sign me up!</p>', 'Suggestions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-14', '', '', '2012-09-05 03:16:35', '2012-09-05 03:16:35', '', 11, 'http://www.brooklynbeans.com/beta//?p=484', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
